Quick instructional on how to use the String Cryptography tool:

1. Encrypting a string.
  a. Enter the string you wish to encrypt in the text area. 
  b1. Add Passkey as you would add a password in the passkey textbox for additional security. This is an optional step. 
  b2. Click Encrypt. 
  c. Retreive your newly-encrypted string from the output text area.
 
2. Decrypting a string.
  a. Enter the string you wish to decrypt in the text area.
  b. If the string has a passkey, enter it. Otherwise leave the field blank.
  c. Click Decrypt.
  c. Retreive your now-decrypted string from the output text area.

Additional information and specifics to be added later.
